subSubSection.paragraph:
Distribution.
The Mediterranean Sea, near the Mahón Island (Baleares Island) (López de la Cuadra & García- Gómez 2001); Gulf of Cádiz (Gazul, Tarsis, and Pipoca MVs) (present study). The colonies from Cádiz were collected from different sea bottoms. At the Gazul MV, the sea bottom is characterized by abundant authigenic carbonates, harboring cold-water coral banks and sponge aggregations. At Tarsis and Pipoca MVs, mixed sea bottoms present sparse authigenic carbonates with small gorgonians (

Swiftia

), while soft bottoms are colonized by sea pens (

Kophobelemnon, Pennatula

), scleractinians (

Flabellum

), and echinoids (

Cidaris cidaris

).
